===Etymology===
c. 18th c., from French ''ogre'', from Latin [[Orcus]], 'god of the underworld', from Greek {{term|Όρκος|sc=polytonic|tr=Horkos}}, the personified demon of oaths ({{term|ὅρκος|sc=polytonic||oath}}) who inflicts punishment upon perjurers.

